<br>
~What on earth is going to happen...~<br>
<br>
::With a shaking hand, Persephone reaches down and takes the sceptor into her left hand. As her small hands grab the cold sceptor, she begins to tremble while maintaining the sceptor's powers. While keeping her eye on the sceptor, she reaches over and picks up her royal crown. Placing the crown on her head, she cries out a little as the powers of the sceptor are are nourished by the crown itself. As if struck by an electric shock, Persephone's eyes widen, her golden eyes turning to two black orbs. As a new grey aura surrounds her, her long dark hairs become an ivory white, her fair skin becoming pale and cold. (OOC: she looks a lot like that elf queen in Lord of the Rings/the fellowship when she snaps over the offered ring, heh.)<br>
<br>
::As hundreds of souls invade the throne room, Persephone, with great struggle, holds the sceptor towards them. as the sceptor works its way to its energetic peak, a white and amethyst light pours out diminishing each soul in its path. As the sceptor becomes its own, Persephone's arm is instantly raised up. Holding on to it as hard as she can, she holds on to the immaculate power. As she uses all her might, the light breaks out blinding the entire room. While the light emerges from the sceptor, Persephone squeezes her eyes shut and screams as the light erupts from the Palace, enlightening the entire Underworld, both Tartarus and the Elysian Fields diminishing every rebelling soul...:: <p>*~* Persephone...Queen of the Underworld.. Faithful wife to Hades... Princess Goddess of the Spring*~*</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ixlordhadesxi>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 218<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/16/03 12:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Proud</span><hr size=1> ::Hades stood patiently, as Persephone left the room. He continued to contemplate when he noticed the surge. Though his Shade-like form felt very little, he watched his physical body spasm slightly. He knew that his power was being shared...he knew the power had found another means of release, since it was apparently being blocked by his own body. He saw the light begin to engulf the room of the palace::<br>
